&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div&gt;The Enrollment Advisor is the first member of the Revero team that prospective patients speak with during the enrollment process. Their job is to help people understand the benefits of the Revero program and how it can help them to achieve their goals. The Enrollment Advisor&amp;nbsp;is meant to be a resource, supporter and source of information to make things easy for prospective patients throughout the onboarding process.&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot;&gt;
&lt;div&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul class=&quot;posting-requirements plain-list&quot;&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct Intake Calls with prospective patients, explaining how the Revero programs works and generating excitement to start the program&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor patient progress through the onboarding pipeline and ensure that patients are moving through the enrollment process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help with logistics&amp;nbsp;including scheduling provider onboarding calls and following up to make sure accurate health information has been submitted by the patient&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help patients to schedule labs if needed and submit lab orders on behalf of patients&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Get patients over the finish line and be an ongoing source of support and assistance&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;section page-centered&quot;&gt;
